German Companies Well Prepared for Slowdown, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   A n d r e a s   C r e m e r
-- 
2011-10-06T05:20:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-06/german-companies-well-prepared-for-slowdown-handelsblatt-says.html
German companies including Porsche
SE, Infineon Technologies AG and ThyssenKrupp AG are well
prepared for a potential economic slowdown,  Handelsblatt 
reported, citing the country’s DIHK business lobby.  “German companies have learned a lesson from the first
major wave of the financial crisis,” the newspaper quoted
Volker Treier, economist at the Berlin-based DIHK industry and
trade chambers as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andreas Cremer in Berlin at 
 acremer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
